parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of recall repairs can lead to continued exposure to safety risks, causing accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Repeated notifications of recall
dealerships stating parts are not available
lack of communication from manufacturers or dealerships
and inability to schedule repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of Takata airbags can cause serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Notification of Takata airbag recall
dealerships stating parts are not available
inability to schedule repairs
and continued exposure to safety risks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake system failures can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Spongy brake pedal
delayed brake response
and inability to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop as needed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HCU can cause the brake system to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances or loss of braking ability.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop as needed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing the recalled brake system can cause the vehicle to remain in an unsafe condition, putting the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: The brake system is still faulty despite receiving a recall notice
the repair parts are not available
the dealer is unable to perform the repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETB can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or hesitate, leading to a loss of control, which can increase the risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly loses power
stalls
or hesitates while driving
the "wrench" light on the dashboard illuminates
the vehicle's RPMs fluctuate
and the vehicle may shut off or restart on its own.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PCM can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or hesitate, leading to a loss of control, which can increase the risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly loses power
stalls
or hesitates while driving
the "check engine" light on the dashboard illuminates
the vehicle's RPMs fluctuate
and the vehicle may shut off or restart on its own.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or hesitate, leading to a loss of control, which can increase the risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle's transmission slips or hesitates while shifting gears
the vehicle's RPMs fluctuate
and the vehicle may shut off or restart on its own.
